Data Set: Promastigote Form Origins of Replication -early S and late S vs G2 (SE)
Contact institution: The Wellcome Centre for Integrative Parasitology
Summary: Origins of replication in L. major Friedlin determined by Marker Frequency Analysis, a technique that compares frequency of marker sequences in replicating and non-replicating cells. Whole genome DNA-Seq of FACS sorted promastigotes is presented as the ratio (S- vs G2-phase) of the frequencies of markers (DNA-Seq reads) in 2.5 kb bins.
